    "explanation": "We use Kadane's algorithm. We iterate through the array, keeping track of the current subarray sum. If the sum drops below zero, we reset it, as any prefix with a negative sum will only decrease the sum of a following subarray. O(N) time, O(1) space.",
    "answer": "def solve(nums):\n    maxSub = nums[0]\n    curSum = 0\n    for n in nums:\n        if curSum < 0: curSum = 0\n        curSum += n\n        maxSub = max(maxSub, curSum)\n    return maxSub",
